1
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:42,060
=Twin Fire Dawn=

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:45,060
=Episode 25=

3
00:00:54,860 --> 00:00:55,780
What?

4
00:00:56,140 --> 00:00:58,620
Don't want to know
where Zhuang Yunqiu is?

5
00:01:04,620 --> 00:01:07,540
The biggest weakness here
is a soft heart.

6
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:10,140
If there was really intent to kill,
it would've happened long ago.

7
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,939
It would've never come to the point
where the closest brother

8
00:01:12,940 --> 00:01:14,020
ended up dead.

9
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:16,980
It was that mercy

10
00:01:17,020 --> 00:01:18,380
that killed him.

11
00:01:23,620 --> 00:01:24,660
Why?

12
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:27,179
Why hurt

13
00:01:27,180 --> 00:01:29,699
everyone close to me?

14
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,780
Why?

15
00:01:31,460 --> 00:01:33,099
That's exactly what I want to ask.

16
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:34,939
Why did we grow up together,

17
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:37,060
yet Cheng Yi was always by your side?

18
00:01:37,220 --> 00:01:39,540
Why was I the older brother
and you the younger?

19
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,980
You went off to war and earned glory.

20
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:45,340
Why did we clearly look alike,

21
00:01:47,020 --> 00:01:49,660
yet Mother always favored you?

22
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:52,860
Here.

23
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:53,419
Eat.

24
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:54,339
Thanks, Mom.

25
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:55,380
It's really sweet.

26
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,300
Mom, have some too.

27
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:10,579
Cheng Yi, you're here.

28
00:02:10,580 --> 00:02:12,420
Shaoyuan, this is for you.

29
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:16,900
I want one too.

30
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:18,540
Can I give it to my brother?

31
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:20,139
No, there's only one.

32
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,780
I only wanted to give it to you.

33
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:26,900
Where did this come from?

34
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,380
You brat, stealing my things now?

35
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:30,860
Where else could it come from?
Stole it from me.

36
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:32,460
Who told you to steal?

37
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:35,160
I'm sorry. He's just a child
and doesn't understand.

38
00:02:36,780 --> 00:02:38,300
Why steal someone else's things?

39
00:02:38,620 --> 00:02:41,540
Because I really
wanted to give this to Mom.

40
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:45,459
Stealing at such a young age?

41
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:47,540
What will become of Gu Shaoyan later on?

42
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:49,859
Mom doesn't need any gift.

43
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,379
Mom only wants you to be obedient

44
00:02:51,380 --> 00:02:52,419
like your brother.

45
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:54,139
As long as you stop causing trouble.

46
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:54,939
I did nothing wrong.

47
00:02:54,940 --> 00:02:58,059
Only stole a little money.
There used to be plenty of money at home.

48
00:02:58,060 --> 00:03:00,580
Now there's none.
What's wrong with taking some from them?

49
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:01,260
You...

50
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:03,540
You...

51
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,400
Let's see if I beat you today.

52
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,659
- Still talking back after stealing?
- I did nothing wrong!

53
00:03:07,660 --> 00:03:09,480
I'll beat you to death!
Admit the mistake or not?

54
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,339
I did nothing wrong.

55
00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:12,860
- Still daring to argue? Today I will...
- Mom, you're unfair!

56
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,500
You only love him, not me!

57
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:15,779
You...

58
00:03:15,780 --> 00:03:17,739
- I did nothing wrong!
- Let's see if I beat you!

59
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:19,500
I did nothing wrong!

60
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:26,660
This is all my fault.

61
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,980
If there's anger, take it out on me.

62
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:33,560
Don't drag innocent people into this.

63
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:35,260
Innocent?

64
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:42,500
As if you're the only one with feelings.

65
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:45,820
Feelings exist here too.

66
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:50,020
That's why a gift was prepared.

67
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,620
Yunqiu.

68
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:03,060
Put the gun down.

69
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:15,540
If you don't want her dead,

70
00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:17,500
hand over the military seal.

71
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,020
Let her go.

72
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:25,340
Then I'll say where the seal is.

73
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,700
Tell me.

74
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:34,420
The military seal

75
00:04:34,620 --> 00:04:37,560
is beneath the pocket at the twelve
o'clock direction on the billiard table.

76
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:46,860
If Lieutenant Li can't find it,

77
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,540
she'll be in danger.

78
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:01,100
Commander,

79
00:05:01,660 --> 00:05:02,420
it's been found.

80
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:09,140
Excellent.

81
00:05:09,380 --> 00:05:12,220
Now Commander Cheng Yi is back again.

82
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:15,620
Although it doesn't sound
as nice as Gu Nianchi,

83
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:19,740
Commander Cheng sounds pretty good too.

84
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:21,860
The thing you wanted is yours now.

85
00:05:22,740 --> 00:05:23,700
Release her.

86
00:05:27,140 --> 00:05:28,340
Shaoyuan,

87
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:29,699
such a beauty...

88
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:30,700
Don't touch her!

89
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:33,860
How could I bear to let go?

90
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,740
Don't worry.

91
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:39,260
She'll be cherished properly.

92
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,140
Gu Shaoyan!

93
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:44,300
You're shameless!

94
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:49,140
How many times does it need to be said?
My name isn't Gu Shaoyan.

95
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,540
My name is Cheng Yi!

96
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,060
You don't deserve that name!

97
00:06:25,180 --> 00:06:26,620
What?

98
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:30,820
Let him go! You're insane!

99
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:32,940
Feeling sorry for him?

100
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:36,140
Compared to the pain of being
stabbed again and again by you,

101
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,380
what does this knife count for?

102
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:39,820
Gu Shaoyan.

103
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:42,700
If you want to kill or torture someone,
come at me!

104
00:06:43,420 --> 00:06:44,620
Don't touch her.

105
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:49,820
Then that wish will be granted first.

106
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:51,020
What are you doing?

107
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:53,020
What are you doing?!

108
00:06:56,020 --> 00:06:58,100
Why treat Cheng Yi so well?

109
00:06:59,660 --> 00:07:00,580
Stop!

110
00:07:03,660 --> 00:07:04,379
Stop it!

111
00:07:04,380 --> 00:07:05,059
Why?

112
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,220
Stop!

113
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:15,220
Why did Mother always favor you?

114
00:07:35,620 --> 00:07:36,580
Lu Shaoyuan.

115
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:37,780
Lu Shaoyuan...

116
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:44,980
What will it take to let him go?

117
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:48,540
Does it hurt?

118
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:51,020
Does it feel painful?

119
00:07:53,740 --> 00:07:54,740
Fine.

120
00:07:55,660 --> 00:07:57,780
Then I'll start by tormenting your body,

121
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:00,780
then the heart.

122
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:02,860
Let him taste it too,

123
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:06,740
the feeling of having
the most beloved thing stolen away.

124
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:09,099
(I need to find a way out.)

125
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:10,260
(If this keeps going,)

126
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:12,300
(even if Gu Shaoyan
doesn't beat him to death,)

127
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:13,980
(he'll be tortured to death by him.)

128
00:08:14,620 --> 00:08:15,780
I have something to say.

129
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,459
♪Carved through endless hardship♪

130
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:20,700
What is it?

131
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:22,380
I know you hate him.

132
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:24,260
But he's still your brother.

133
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,180
There's no point
in torturing him like this.

134
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:27,100
How about this?

135
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,420
Kill me instead.

136
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:31,100
I'm the person he cares
about most in this world.

137
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:33,820
After I die, make him live
the rest of his life alone.

138
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,420
Let him suffer for the rest of his life.

139
00:08:35,420 --> 00:08:36,380
Wouldn't that be better?

140
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:42,019
♪This heart and love slowly fade away♪

141
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:44,220
Darling, that does
remind me of something.

142
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:46,700
You kill him.

143
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:48,980
That way, not only will he die,

144
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:50,660
it'll hurt him even more.

145
00:08:52,380 --> 00:08:54,059
Then why not just kill both of us?

146
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:55,540
Why go through all this trouble?

147
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:57,340
Of course it's different.

148
00:08:57,980 --> 00:08:59,980
One of you kills the other,

149
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:02,700
and the other dies by the hand
of the person they love most.

150
00:09:03,340 --> 00:09:05,380
Wouldn't that make the pain even worse?

151
00:09:05,460 --> 00:09:08,399
♪Even if time has given up on us♪

152
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:11,599
♪I still long to hold you once again♪

153
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,719
♪When love runs deep,
why fear growing old together?♪

154
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:18,899
♪Let the frost wither
the greenery beyond the window♪

155
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:19,980
I don't want to die.

156
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,420
If I kill him,

157
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,180
will you let me go?

158
00:09:24,380 --> 00:09:25,700
Don't try anything funny.

159
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,300
If you can't kill him,

160
00:09:28,940 --> 00:09:30,980
then I'll slowly torture him.

161
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:33,500
I'll gouge out his eyes.

162
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,740
I'll make him wish he were dead.

163
00:09:55,340 --> 00:10:00,030
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

164
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:06,660
♪How much hope must fade into despair?♪

165
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:10,740
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

166
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:14,090
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

167
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:19,380
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

168
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:25,690
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

169
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:32,350
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

170
00:10:32,890 --> 00:10:36,270
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

171
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:39,469
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

172
00:10:39,470 --> 00:10:44,609
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

173
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:48,929
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

174
00:10:48,930 --> 00:10:51,509
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

175
00:10:51,510 --> 00:10:53,789
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

176
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:57,339
♪The right to be loved by you?♪

177
00:10:57,340 --> 00:11:01,869
♪If love is nothing
more than endless schemes♪

178
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:04,400
♪Used and abandoned in the end♪

179
00:11:04,540 --> 00:11:06,489
♪Still I walk into♪

180
00:11:06,490 --> 00:11:10,089
♪The trap you set without regret♪

181
00:11:10,090 --> 00:11:14,139
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

182
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:16,719
♪Yet keep it buried deep inside♪

183
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,879
♪A stand in can never cross♪

184
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:22,319
♪The shortest distance between us♪

185
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:27,290
♪If love can
make someone lose themselves♪

186
00:11:27,450 --> 00:11:32,120
♪Then let me stay by your side♪

187
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:36,469
♪A substitute♪

188
00:11:36,470 --> 00:11:41,470
♪Needs no reason♪

